projectSectionHintDesc.message: The basis of your project management. Here you can create a new project, rename it, and close a project.

blocksHintDesc.message:
Every synecto project includes the following features::
Tasks - here you can manage your work process, define, assign and manage tasks, set task variables such as due dates, difficulty levels, labels and much more
Files - the cloud drive allows you to create, store and manage all your project ÃÅs folders and files;
Chat - here you can communicate live with your project ÃÅs team members;
Archive - here you can archive and restore any project ÃÅs document.

membersHintDesc.message: Here the project owner can add and manage his or her project team members. Anyone can join the team. Simply invite clients, colleagues, collaborators or friends for example.

userMenuDesc.message: Simply click on your email address and your settings menu opens. Here you can manage your account, your synecto customer plan, and contact support. The bell icon to the left highlights all your notifications.

taskListDesc.message: You can add new task here. Any task list has quick filters, they located on top of it. By default quick filter shows only "not completed" tasks.

assigneeHintDesc.message: Clicking this button you can assign some team member on this task. Task assignee can change task status and track time spent on this task.

statusHintDesc.message:
There are 4 statuses in Synecto:
Awaiting - when task is not start.
In progress - when assignee start working.
Completed - When task is finished.
Expired - when task is not completed by due date.

taskActionsDesc.message: Change due date, estimate tasks in story points, track spent time, and others

subtasksHintDesc.message: Type new subtask name and press Enter. Use breadcrumbs to navigate between task and subtasks.

folderHintDesc.message: You can open any folder by double clicking it. Breadcrumbs allow you to easily and quickly view and navigate through your folders. When you click the three vertical dots (folder menu buttons) or when you right-click on a folder the folder options menu opens

fsPanelHintDesc.message: Here the features allow you to create a new folder, upload a new file and create Google documents

fileHintDesc.message: Images can be discussed using precise comments. Office files (docx,xlsx,pttx,pdf) can be previewed. Using context menu you can copy file #ID to create link on it in comments.

attachFileChatDesc.message: Upload a new file or attach an existing file from the file system. Newly uploaded files here will automatically be stored in the file system

attachTaskChatHintDesc.message: Create a new task or attach an existing task from the task manager. Newly created tasks here will automatically be saved in the task manager
